    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street | Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1887-04-20">April 20 '87</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear R W G</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours enclosing Mr Carnegie's<ptr target="loc.03486_n1"/> magnificent contribution to
                me (&#38; to the Lincoln memory lecture) of $350 has safely come to hand. I thank
                A[ndrew] C[arnegie] from my heart&#8212;The money, of course, will help me every way
                &#38; practically, &#38; is appreciated for its source in kindest human good
                will.</p>
            <p>I thank you, too, dear friend&#8212;your faithful heart &#38; voice&#8212;I wish this
                note sent to Mr Carnegie with my gratitude and love.<ptr target="nyp.00574_n1"/></p>

            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
